## Pivot Table Findings

### Revenue by Brand

Revenue analysis identified Eufy as the highest revenue-generating brand, followed by Annke, Zosi, and Sannce.

Placeholder brand values such as "Unknown" and "Unbranded/Generic" contributed meaningful revenue, supporting the earlier decision to preserve these records during data cleaning.

### Revenue by Primary Category

IP/Smart Camera Systems generated the highest estimated revenue, followed by Security Cameras.

These findings suggest that smart surveillance products represent the dominant revenue source within the dataset.

### Revenue by Product Type

Camera and Bullet Camera products generated the largest share of revenue.

Complete surveillance systems also contributed significantly to overall revenue performance.

### Revenue by Seller

Revenue distribution was concentrated among a relatively small group of sellers, with Seller_4 generating the highest estimated revenue.

### Revenue by Smart Home Ecosystem

Products classified as Other/Generic generated the largest share of revenue, followed by the Eufy ecosystem.

This suggests a substantial portion of products operate independently of major smart-home platforms or were categorized using generic ecosystem labels.

All column-retention decisions are being documented to preserve analytical transparency.


