## Revenue Metric Development

To support ecommerce performance analysis, a new calculated field named `estimated_revenue` was created in the Working_Data sheet.

Formula:

Estimated Revenue = Price × Units Sold

The field was added to allow revenue-focused analysis including:

- Revenue by Brand
- Revenue by Product Type
- Revenue by Category
- Top Revenue Products
- Revenue Distribution Analysis

The calculated field was created in the working copy of the dataset while preserving the original raw dataset.

KPIs include:

- Total Products
- Total Units Sold
- Total Inventory Available
- Average Product Price
- Average Discount Percentage
- Total Savings USD
- Estimated Revenue

These metrics provide a high-level overview of marketplace performance before detailed analysis and SQL querying.

The difference between average and median prices suggests the presence of higher-priced products influencing the overall distribution.

